For the bivariate, there is some transaformations to be done, We are creating another column that would have just Completed and defaulted from the Loan status column.¶

In [29]:
def transform(df):
    
    if df['LoanStatus'] == 'Completed':
         return 'Completed'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Chargedoff': #loan is considered “charged-off” after a borrower misses 5 consecutive monthly payments
        #We would consider this also Defaulted
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Defaulted':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (1-15 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (91-120 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (61-90 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (31-60 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (16-30 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    elif df['LoanStatus'] == 'Past Due (>120 days)':
        return 'Defaulted'
    else:
        return 'Not Applicable'

  • Chart B1 shows that the employed(including fully employed) borrowers are more, and they also have more borrowers withing the A-C rating.

  • More of the borrowers who have completely fulfil their obligations have the rating 'A'

  • Borrowers with 'AA' rating seldomly default on their obligations to repay their loans.

  • The Prosper ratings of the borrower's affect the loan amount is granted, the 'AA' and 'A' rated borrowers have more average proincipal borrowed compared to the borrowers in other rating band.

  • Both Home Owner status and Employment status have an impact on the ability of the borrower to fulful their obligation.

  • There is a relationship between the borrower's prosper score and their respective rate.

  • Employment status of the borrower does not affect the borrower's rate or prosper score.

Conclusions¶

  • The distribution of the Monthly income of the borrowers as stated by them shows that the median of the data is around USD 5,000 , which means that most of the borrowers earn around USD5k on an average.

  • The distribution of the borrower's rating show that the A rated borrowers are more that all the other ratings.

  • More of the borrowers who have completely fulfil their obligations have the rating 'A'

  • The average amount borrowed to home owners with high prosper rating is clearly more than homeowners with prosper rating, same also apply for borrowers who don't own a home.

  • The Prosper ratings of the borrower's affect the loan amount is granted, the 'AA' and 'A' rated borrowers have more average principal borrowed compared to the borrowers in other rating band.

  • The unemployed borrowers have a 'D' rating

  • Borrowers with 'AA' rating seldomly default on their obligations to repay their loans.

  • Both Home Owner status and Employment status have an impact on the ability of the borrower to fulful their obligation.
